              <h2><a name="kids_helping_kids"></a>Kids Helping Kids   </h2>
              

              <table width="221" height="136" border="0" align="left" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0">
                <tr>
                  <td width="221" height="136"><span class="note"><img src="../images/hold-hands.gif" width="200" height="116" hspace="10" vspace="10" border="0"></span></td>
                </tr>
            </table>
              <p>At Club Penguin, we&rsquo;re committed to improving the lives of children everywhere by supporting organizations doing important work on behalf of the world&rsquo;s youngest and most vulnerable citizens. </p>
              <p> A portion of the proceeds from every Club  Penguin membership is used to   support specific local and global projects. 
                Currently, our funds are focused on two building projects in a small Ugandan village and a children&rsquo;s hospital project in Romania. </p>
              <p> Supporting these projects is our way of allowing the kids who join Club Penguin to play a role in securing a happier and healthier future for other children around the globe. It&rsquo;s kids helping kids, something we can all be proud of. </p>
			  <p>We are currently organizing a non-profit foundation to manage the specifics of each project we undertake. This will allow us to provide you with more detailed, timely updates on projects and the difference these projects are making in many kids lives. Check back for updates. </p>
			  <p> Current Projects:</p>
              <ul>
                <li><a href="#uganda">Uganda</a></li>
                <li><a href="#romania">Romania</a></li>
              </ul>
			  <div align="right"><a href="#top">back to top</a></div>
			  <h2><a name="uganda"></a>Uganda</h2>
              <p><strong><img src="../images/kids.jpg" width="250" height="188" hspace="10" align="right"></strong>                  Club Penguin&rsquo;s newest <em>Kids Helping Kids </em>project will improve the lives of   African children orphaned by AIDS and war.<br>
                  <br>
                  <strong> Education </strong></p>
              <p>We are working with an organization in Uganda to help provide scholarships,   project funding and learning resources to improve education opportunities for   students across the country. We are planning a pilot project, &#8220;Kids Helping Kids   Resource Center&#8221; to address the need for children to have FREE access to   quality educational and academic resources, including but not limited to:   computers, internet, age-appropriate reading materials, and a safe place to   explore.<br>
                <br>
                <strong> Health Care </strong></p>
              <p>We have committed to build a medical facility in Fort Portal that will provide   children better access to basic medical treatment. We have also helped equip a medical clinic in Rwebisengo, a village along the Ugandan border with Congo.<BR>
                <br>
                For more information about our work in Uganda,  please contact
